9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1111, L.D. 1676, “Resolve, to Study
10 Ways to Improve Recruitment and Retention of Rural Emergency Medical Services
11 Personnel Through Access to Health Insurance”
12 Amend the resolve by striking out the title and substituting the following:
13 'Resolve, to Study Ways to Improve Recruitment and Retention of Rural Emergency
14 Services Personnel'
15 Amend the resolve in section 1 in the last line (page 1, line 3 in L.D.) by striking out
16 the following: "medical services personnel through access to health insurance" and
17 inserting the following: 'services personnel including, but not limited to, emergency
18 medical services persons, volunteer or part-time firefighters and health care workers'
19 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 1 in paragraph A in the 2nd line (page 1,
20 line 8 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "services" the following: 'or firefighting'
21 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 1 by inserting after paragraph B the
22 following:
23 'C. One member who represents a statewide association of volunteer firefighters;'
24 Amend the resolve in section 2 in subsection 1 by relettering the paragraphs to read
25 alphabetically.
26 Amend the resolve by striking out all of section 3 and inserting the following:
27 'Sec. 3. Duties. Resolved: That the commission shall study ways to improve
28 recruitment and retention of emergency services personnel in rural areas of the State. In its
29 study, the commission may examine all benefits that may incentivize the recruitment and
30 retention of rural emergency services personnel, which must include, at a minimum:
31 1. Increased access to health insurance;
32 2. Financial incentives including stipends, tuition assistance and loan forgiveness;
33 3. Increased access to mental health support;
