COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 1111, L.D. 1676
1 4. Retirement contributions or service credits;
2 5. Volunteer recognition and professional advancement pathways; and
3 6. An examination of the recommendations made by the Municipal Volunteer Working
4 Group as established by Resolve 2015, chapter 49. This examination must include a review
5 of that working group's recommendations that have been implemented and whether the
6 recommendations that have not been implemented are still appropriate.'
7 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
8 section number to read consecutively.
9 SUMMARY
1100 This amendment, which is the minority report of the committee, changes the title and
1111 expands the scope of the resolve to include emergency medical services persons, volunteer
1122 or part-time firefighters and health care workers. The amendment also provides additional
1133 detail on what issues the commission should examine to improve recruitment and retention
1144 of these individuals, including increased access to health insurance, financial incentives,
1155 increased access to mental health support, retirement benefits and professional
1166 advancement pathways, and directs the commission to review the recommendations made
1177 by the Municipal Volunteer Working Group as established by Resolve 2015, chapter 49 to
1188 determine whether those recommendations are still appropriate.
